      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MOTOR CITY ROSSI (2) was well off top last time, finishing 6th (30.29) in a Grade 4/5 at Sandown. Has won here at this journey. Can make amends. LASSARD (1) was quickly into stride and burnt early from out wide where he gave a sight, finishing second (25.53) and beaten 4 lengths over 450m at Ballarat. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Bold showing expected. BAYWARA (3) was safely held last time out, finishing seventh at Sandown over 515m behind Ulenta Bale (30.32) in a Grade 5. Should be about the money. AMRON SAMMY (4) is always hard to beat when he races at this trip.",
